title: ICE: "fully private item in the table" when compiling bacon v2.2.5

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
``` error: internal compiler error: compiler/rustc_middle/src/middle/privacy.rs:203:17: fully private item in the table DefId(0:881 ~ bacon[0c20]::{use#3}): Restricted(DefId(0:0 ~ bacon[0c20])) --> /home/ben/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/bacon-2.2.5/src/main.rs:38:5 | 38 | app::*, | ^^^ ``` I can't reproduce this on nightly, but I can reproduce it on a toolchain I keep up to date with `master` that is built with debug assertions: `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` cargo 1.67.0-nightly (16b097879 2022-11-14) release: 1.67.0-nightly commit-hash: 16b097879b6f117c8ae698aab054c87f26ff325e commit-date: 2022-11-14 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu libgit2: 1.5.0 (sys:0.15.0 vendored) libcurl: 7.86.0-DEV (sys:0.4.59+curl-7.86.0 vendored ssl:OpenSSL/1.1.1q) os: Arch Linux [64-bit] ```
